summary: This is an automated email notification from the E2Solutions travel system confirming final approval of a travel voucher for an FBI agent's trip related to the Epstein investigation. The trip involved witness interviews in the United States from February 26-29, 2020, with total expenses of $1,196.11.

keyFacts: The document is a financial/travel voucher approval email from the DOJ's E2Solutions system, dated March 24, 2020.
It confirms a trip (ID: 11061409-1) for 'Epstein Investigation Witness interviews' that occurred from February 26 to 29, 2020, with total expenses of $1,196.11.
The traveler is an FBI agent with the surname 'Minor', indicating active investigative work on the Epstein case in early 2020.
The voucher's purpose is listed under a project/customer code 'R20NYS13400', suggesting it was part of a specific, funded investigative effort.
The document demonstrates the ongoing, official government investigation into Epstein matters as of early 2020, involving witness interviews and associated travel expenses.
